            "answer_text": "I'm sure you can. As long as the book wasn't sealed in plastic wrapper, and you finish the book within the return period (usually between 15 to 30 days, which is enough to finish most books).  But why would you do that? If you want to read books but don't want to pay or keep them, you can use public library, which allow you to borrow and read and return a book often free of charge.   ",
