            "author_info": {
                "name": "N Heiser",
                "href": "/profile/N-Heiser"
            },
            "answer_text": "Barnes & Noble has a reasonable book return policy. However, let me take this a different way: do you want bookstores to close down due to lack of profitability? Do you want publishers to go out of business because people are too cheap to pay for a book? Do you want authors to stop writing good books because people are not willing to pay a reasonable amount for those books? How far are you willing to go with being a cheapskate? People are in business to make money. I know you\u2019re not rich, but the book business is not the place to make pay for the bad economy. The profit margin in the book business, at all levels, is so narrow that most in the business are barely squeaking by. How much are you willing to screw them over just to save a few bucks? Don\u2019t be that person. ",
